text: Chak Haryam () is a village, near Islamgarh in the Chakswari tehsil of the Mirpur District in Azad Kashmir, Pakistan. == Demography == According to 1998 census of Pakistan, its population was 973. == History == Like many villages in the Mirpur region, many of its residents have emigrated to the United Kingdom. == References == Category:Villages in Azad Kashmir
title: Chak Haryam
